caption: Finally ordered carry out from Golden Dragon. Tasty and a decent price. I will order from here again.

You have to call to place your order, and then you can pick it up inside or curbside or get delivery. Pick up was super fast over the lunch hour, right at 15 minutes (I can walk there from our downtown Bloomington office) So much food for the price, and the quality is top notch! The beef with broccoli was cooked perfectly, seasoned perfectly and the amount of sauce was just right. Comes with white rice, but you can sub for fried rice with a small fee. It came in the perfect sized container which is microwaveable so if you only want to eat half and save the other half for another lunch day, you're already good to go! The egg roll was the perfect complement and it came with all of the sauces: soy, sweet sour and spicy mustard. I understand now why everyone else in my office is obsessed and goes there regularly. Can't wait to try everything else on the menu!

Super fast and efficient. My wife and I are originally from Houston Texas so this place was above and beyond what our expectations were. Thank you for making the food so delicious! Will definitely be ordering from this restaurant again.
Consistently high quality.

Im so sorry to say that i was disappointed with my order. The noodles in my shrimp lo mein had almost no sauce on them and were very flavorless. I ordered extra shrimp and they did ad them, but they were very over cooked. The egg soup is the best in town tho:)

I love this place! The food is always super fresh and full of flavor and the service is always very good. They are really nice and very efficient, Ive never had a single mistake happen on any of my orders. I recommend the shrimp with mushrooms, shrimp lo mein and all of their delicious soups. Dont forget a pork egg roll next time you stop by:)
Called ahead. Showed up 30 minutes later to be told they hadn't even started, they just forgot. 15 minutes or more to make my food at that point. Very unorganized.
The best Chinese Food and the best people!
We miss you guys!!  Hope you are doing well. Still can’t find any better Chinese food. Hoping to see #goldendragon family these coming seasons.

Staff friendly. Price was very reasonable. They were able to make adjustments to how they made my food and not use ingredients I'm allergic to. Portion size was reasonable. I had enough to eat but no leftovers. So if you are a big eater or want leftovers, you will have to order more than the typical meal. Good was cooked fresh and tasted really good. No deserts. Drinks somewhat limited to choices. But the place was very clean . For some reason Google had it listed as a "Buffet". It's not , so that was disappointing. But that's a Google issue. It's a "mom and pop" kind of establishment and feel. But with that being said. The food was great!!!!
Only chinese place I will eat at in town! Best food and friendly service. Highly recommend!!

I remember coming here 30 odd years ago and the food is just as good as I remembered it. The basic meals (around 5 to 6 dollars)are filling and large but you can basicly super size of with a soup, egg roll, wonton and crab rangoon for an extra 4 dollars. That means for about 10 bucks you get a giant amount of food. I grabbed the wonton soup to start which was full of delicious wontons. I subbed fried rice for the white which was an excellent choice. My beef and mushrooms was incredible. The shrimp and broccoli was even better. I highly suggest the food here as it's incredible. Now the location for eat in has a kind of downfall. I remember it differently back in the day fully decorated and exquisite. Now it's similar to a cafeteria with cheap tables and generic cafeteria chairs. A little decor on the walls but no major ambiance (hince the 4 stars). Grab this place for carry out or get it delivered. It is way better than the local China Star or Panda express and a much better value.

Came by at 7:30 on Saturday, January 18th and the door was locked and they were closed despite hours saying they would be open. What a waste of my time. No sign on door either stating they were closed.
Great food, great prices!
Great environment, great owners, wonderful food. They even ask you how hot you want some dishes, which doesn't always happen.  I recommend giving this place a try.
It's is the perfect hole in the wall location! You'd never find it unless you knew where it was, and it is the best quality food you can find
Large portions, taste is one of best I've had, very reasonable prices, restaurant clean and nice atmosphere
This place has delicious food. It isn't fancy or pretty inside, but the food is just spot on. I have never been disappointed. And priced very reasonably. I recommend it.
I really enjoy the carryout from these folks. Always has good flavor and plenty of food.
Good food for decent price

Utterly awful.  The dipping sauce for the pot stickers was straight soy sauce and onions, no ginger at all, and the pot stickers themselves are under cooked..  The barbecue pork and broccoli comes in a clear, flavorless broth.  The pork slices are fingernail sized, and the rice is very, very old.  I threw most of it away.
Comfortable environment, experienced servers and delicious food. Definitely stop by if you're in town.
Love, love, LOVE their food!! The service is always friendly and fast. Best crab Rangoon ever!
Superfresh food great customer service highly recommend
Food is good. About 8 out of 10 for flavor.  9 out of 10 for value and portion size.  Knocking a star off for charging 50 cents for pop refills.  I mean who does that?
Great service ,Great food and Sue and Kevin are the nicest people you will ever meet! Thumbs up!
Great food, best prices on the planet!
Great atmosphere, delicious food, good prices... love the staff
I've been coming to Golden Dragon over 15 years. The egg rolls are some of the best I've ever had. Kevin and Sue are so kind and provide great service with delicious food.

AFFORDABLE, FAST AND GREAT QUALITY FOOD! The enviroment was nice as well as the staff. I had recently purchased, beef and broccoli, garlic shrimp, sweet n sour chicken and two eggs rolls. With ALL the food i had got, it only paid 22 dollars! It was incredible and the food was amazing. I will definitely be going back and probably making this my main stay.
It was very Good food and great services and great atmosphere also ... This is my 4th time eating there i will go back there and eat...
Good food, poke stop adjacent
Every time I try to eat here, they're closed. Wednesday at 11:30 AM - Closed. Thursday at Noon - Closed. Friday at 5 PM - Closed. I've tried eating here 4 or 5 times and it's never open!
Good food price is fair and the people are very friendly
Good food. Nice friendly employees!
One of my favorite places to eat! Amazing food in a welcoming environment

One of the best sit down Chinese restaurants in town. This is a go-to favorite for me. The environment is always clean and friendly. The owners are always working hard and know their customers well. Perfect spot for a low key lunch run or a casual business meeting.
Amazing food!!!!!
Clean and friendly, but we were underwelmed with the food.
Food is great and cooked fresh. Owners are super nice.
Good food reasonable price
We always enjoy our meals here.  The food is fast and tasty and the owners are really nice people.

The absolute best hunan chicken you can find.  Spicy but you can still enjoy all the different flavors.  The crab rangoon is pretty tasty as well.  Everything is made to order, not sitting in a warming pan under heat lamps.  Takes a minute to get your food but most definitely worth it for freshly made entrees.   They have daily lunch specials but I love the hunan chicken so much I can't order anything else.
Great Food. Great Value. Friendly people.
Best chinese in town!
Good food and good service!

All of the food here is cooked to order, most if not all of the recipes are original to the restaurant. Many are Sue's (co-owner, Kevin's wife) family's recipes that she brought with her from Taiwan. Since they're cooking everything to order, sometimes it may take them a bit longer to get your food to you. However, the slightly longer wait time is well worth it in my opinion. My favorite is the garlic chicken, which is definitely unique to the Golden Dragon. Other Chinese restaurants in town have garlic chicken, but I haven't found one that I like nearly as much as theirs.
Tasty, affordable, and good service. What more do you need? Super nice people. Will be visiting for meal often! :D
Great crab rangon (I can't spell 😂) and cashew chicken. 😊
Great owners with great food!
Lovely atmosphere, quiet and elegant. Very good price for really excellent food!!
Awesome Chinese restaurant always great food and good portions for the money. Friendly, family run restaurant. Been going there for 20+ years, never had a bad meal.
I've eaten here at least once a week for ten years. Great Mom & Pop restaurant.
Love this place.
It was just horrible food. There was also no one in the restaurant.
It was ok. Crab rangoon was very peppery. Garlic chicken is not the best. Fried rice was very good!

I like this place not only because of the food quality, but also because it's part of the dying breed of family run restaurant. It's nice to go in here and always see the same smiling faces working hard and seeming to really enjoy the work. The prices are very good, as is the food.
Always tasty..
Love eating here. Sue and Kevin are the best.  Good great.
Not bad Chinese Food.
Always great food and service. Very nice family run business.
The crab Rangoon has pepper in it, and it's the best Rangoon I've ever had!
Food was ok and fast. 50 cents for a refill on a $1.45 soda though. A little dumb.
Eat there many Fridays. Kevin and Sue make great food and are incredibly kind. Great family owned spot.
Yum!!!  And great people, too!

The food was absolutely gross. Inside the crab Rangoon was hair, my husband ordered sweet and sour pork and they served it to him and the pork was still frozen. The Chicken Lo Mein was the grossest Lo Mein I have ever tried in my life. We will never come back to this place as this was far the grossest Chinese I have ever eaten.
There egg rolls and crab Rangoon are the best you can find in this area!!!
Good Chinese food.  it is always decent clean small restaurant
best chinese food ive ever had in Bloomington IL
I like Americanized Chinese and have visited 25+ restaurants. So far this is the second least favorite. Bland chicken and in general under par.
Called the order in, 20 mins later it was hot and ready.  The food was excellent! Best Chinese in town.
Very good. Friendly service

One of my friends and I systematically tried almost every Chinese restaurant in Bloomington-Normal and after we tried this place, it was hard to move on! The service is always friendly and fast, the prices are reasonable, and the food just tastes better than other Chinese restaurants. Their egg rolls are especially amazing. It's my go-to Chinese place now.
